FFmpeg is the leading multimedia framework, able to decode, encode,
transcode, mux, demux, stream, filter and play pretty much anything
that humans and machines have created. It supports the most obscure
ancient formats up to the cutting edge. It includes libavcodec, the
leading audio/video codec library.

Dependencies natively supported by slackware 15.0

--enable-libfontconfig --enable-libfreetype --enable-libfribidi
--enable-libbluray --enable-libcaca --enable-libcdio --enable-libssh
--enable-libtheora --enable-libv4l2 --enable-libvorbis --enable-libvpx
--enable-libwebp --enable-libmp3lame" --enable-opencl --enable-opengl
--enable-libopenjpeg --enable-libpulse --enable-libsmbclient
--enable-frei0r --enable-libspeex --enable-openal --enable-libopus
--enable-libvidstab --enable-libxml2 --enable-librsvg --enable-libdrm
--enable-vulkan --enable-lcms2

Anyone of deps can be enabled but not both

libglslang or libshaderc
librtmp or libgmp or libgcrypt
openssl or gnutls or mbedtls or libtls
aribb24 or libaribcaption [use libaribcaption]

Needed newer version: --enable-liblensfun

broken: opencv4 and pocketsphinx

Added to current but not in stable and available in SBo

--enable-libaom --enable-libdav1d --enable-libass --enable-libplacebo

is it needed"

--enable-decklink --enable-libtesseract  --enable-librabbitmq"
 --enable-libklvanc  --enable-libjack  --enable-libopenvino
  --enable-libqrencode   --enable-libquirc --enable-librav1e
  --enable-libtensorflow  --enable-libtorch


need to enable these flags:

--enable-gpl --enable-nonfree

available in SBo

--enable-libx264 --enable-libcelt --enable-libdc1394 --enable-libgsm
--enable-libxvid --enable-libiec61883 --enable-libilbc --enable-libmodplug
--enable-libtwolame --enable-ladspa --enable-libflite --enable-libx265
--enable-libzvbi --enable-libgme --enable-libsnappy --enable-libzmq
--enable-libbs2b --enable-librubberband  --enable-lv2
--enable-libcodec2 --enable-libsoxr --enable-libsrt --enable-libzimg
--enable-chromaprint --enable-vapoursynth --enable-libopencore-amrnb
--enable-libopencore-amrwb --enable-libfdk-aac --enable-libaribb24
--enable-libjxl --enable-librist --enable-libshine --enable-libsvtav1
--enable-libmysofa --enable-libxavs2 --enable-libvmaf

--enable-libvpl enable Intel oneVPL code via libvpl if libmfx is not used


other os features to be disabled

--disable-appkit  --disable-avfoundation  --disable-coreimage
-disable-metal --disable-audiotoolbox [apple os]
--disable-sndio [bsd]
--disable-schannel  --disable-securetransport
--disable-d3d11va   --disable-d3d12va --disable-dxva2 [windows]
 [only needed if nvidia gpu is used]
 --disable-cuda-llvm
  --disable-cuvid --disable-ffnvcodec --disable-nvdec --disable-nvenc
--disable-amf  [amd gpu]
--disable-large-tests --disable-valgrind-backtrace


